## Pre-Submission Checklist

| # | Check | How to Verify |
|---|-------|---------------|
| 1 | HF Space deploys, `/reset` returns 200 | `curl -X POST https://your-space.hf.space/reset` |
| 2 | `openenv validate` passes | `cd meta-hackthon && openenv validate` |
| 3 | `docker build .` succeeds | `docker build -t cloud-resource-env:latest .` |
| 4 | `inference.py` runs, produces scores | `python inference.py` — check stdout format |
| 5 | 3 tasks with graders, scores 0.0–1.0 | Each `[END]` line has valid score |
| 6 | Env vars defined | Check `.env.example` matches spec |
| 7 | Runtime < 20min on vcpu=2, mem=8gb | Time the full inference run |

---

## Infrastructure Constraints

| Constraint | Limit | Our Approach |
|------------|-------|-------------|
| CPU | 2 vCPUs | NumPy-only physics (no GPU), lightweight |
| Memory | 8 GB | No PyTorch in server mode; torch only for demo |
| Inference time | < 20 min | 3 tasks × ~50-200 steps × 1 LLM call/step ≈ 5-10 min |
| Docker image | Must build | python:3.10-slim base, minimal deps |

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated (before submission)
1. `openenv validate` → must pass
2. `docker build -t cloud-resource-env:latest .` → must succeed
3. `docker run -p 7860:7860 cloud-resource-env:latest` → server starts
4. `curl -X POST http://localhost:7860/reset` → returns 200 + observation JSON
5. `python inference.py` → produces valid `[START]/[STEP]/[END]` output
6. All 3 task grader scores in 0.0–1.0 range

### Manual
1. Gradio demo still works (`MODE=demo`)
2. DQN training still works (`python q_agent.py --train`)
3. HF Space is accessible and responds
